         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ It will interest Mr Bentham and yourself for the genera, that Luisia and Eria are represented in N. E. Australia, and perhaps Epiblema in N. Zealand; for the latter, indicated by Mr Buchanan, ¶  I ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.04.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Library.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">When transcribed, the MS was bound in Hooker's interleaved copy of Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 3, part 2, issued in 1883<seg style="color: #000000; ">, between pp. 830 and 831, i.e. within the treatment of the </seg>Liliaceae, not the Orchidaceae where it would have been better placed. When called up to enable the transcription to be checked, the volume could not be found. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation in pencil: 'Shown to Mr Bentham'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The item is dated to April 1882 as the earliest date it could have been written, as M evidently became aware in that month of Buchanan's announcement of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>
                     </seg> being found in New Zealand (see M to J. Buchanan, 17 April 1882 (in this edition as 82-04-17a)). It was probably written before M commented on the text of Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 3, part 2, because in his acknowledgement of a copy (M to J. Hooker, 1 June 1883), he included comments on genera recognised therein, including reiterating that <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Eria">Eria</name>
                     </seg> (listed on p. 509) and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Luisia">Luisia</name>
                     </seg> (p. 571) had 'genuine Australian species'; there was no comment on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>
                     </seg>, which had been listed (p. 607) as a New Zealand genus, found by W. L. Travers who was the source of Buchanan's specimen.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It will interest Mr Bentham and yourself for the genera, that <name key="Luisia">Luisia</name> and <name key="Eria">Eria</name> are represented in N. E. Australia, and perhaps <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name> in N. Zealand; for the latter, indicated by Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Buchanan (1882), p. 357.</p>
               </note> I cannot vouch, as I have not seen any specimen, but <name key="Calochilus">Calochilus</name> does certainly occur there.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Calochilus">Calochilus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epiblema">Epiblema</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eria">Eria</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Luisia">Luisia</name>
            </p>
